<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870604-0151 </DOCNO><HL> Three-Firm Drilling GroupDiscovers Oil, Gas in Egypt</HL><DD> 06/04/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MDEST DD TEICCPETROLEUM (PET)NATURAL GAS, PIPELINES (LNG) </IN><DATELINE> OKLAHOMA CITY  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Texas International Co. disclosed two oil and gas discoveries in Egypt's western desert.    It said the wells are 75%-owned by Egyptian General Petroleum Corp., the Egyptian government's oil company; 12.5%-owned by Conoco Inc., a Du Pont Co. unit; and 12.5%-owned by Texas International. The wells are operated by Khalda Petroleum Co., a joint venture of the three companies.    Texas International said the Yasser No. 1 discovery well reached a daily rate of 8,941 barrels of oil and 13.6 million cubic feet of natural gas with a one-inch choke. It said the Amoun No. 2 discovery well produced 4,160 barrels of oil and 12.5 million cubic feet of natural gas daily through a three-quarter-inch choke.    Texas International said &quot;further drilling will be required to evaluate the discoveries.&quot; </TEXT></DOC>